			<p>Drupal 8 and Pattern Lab both use Twig templates. Twig is a PHP templating engine which is part of the <a href="https://symfony.com/" target="_blank">Symfony</a> framework. Twig is sort of like the Sass of PHP.</p>
			<p>Twig has thee main delimiters that are used to build code. You can write expressions (variable outputs, strings, Twig functions, etc) using <span class="code">{{ expression }}</span>. You can execute statements with tags such as if, for (loops) and set (define variable) using <span class="code">{{ execute }}</span>. Comments are adding using <span class="code">{{ comment }}</span>. Whenever using a Twig delimiter in a template, it is preferable to separate the opening and closing part of the delimiter from the content using a space on each side: <span class="code">{{ expressionEx }}</span> or <span class="code">{{ executeEx }}</span></p>
			<p>Twig templates should be commented use descriptive comments (<span class="code">{{ commentEx }}</span></span>) the same as you would JS or Scss to explain your code to other developers (or future you from 6 months from now). Template name comments are not needed since templates are not compiled into single files like Scss. Component section name comments are recommended when using <a href="https://twig.symfony.com/doc/2.x/functions/block.html" target="_blank">Twig blocks</a>.</p>
			<p>Contrib modules like <a href="https://www.drupal.org/project/twig_tweak" target="_blank">Twig Teak</a> and <a href="https://www.drupal.org/project/twig_extensions" target="_blank">Twig Extensions</a> help expand the native Drupal Twig functions. Twig Tweak is an OC Patterns dependency and used to insert media entities with the <span class="code">drupal_entity()</span> function and Drupal Blocks with <span class="code">drupal_block()</span>. Twig tweak is also what proves the <span class="code">dd()</span> variable dump function used in custom templating.</p>
			<p>Twig Extensions is used on as needed basis to introduce text and array functions and filters like <span class="code">|truncate</span> and <span class="code">|shuffle</span>.</p>
